Thoracic spiracles brown, relatively large; legs brown to dark brown; proepisternal depression usually with pale setae; rim and disc of upper and lower calypters brown; base of wing with veins and cells dark brown, rest of wing hyaline; basicosta and tegula brown and black respectively; subcostal sclerite brown with brown pubescence; presutural area of the thorax with heavy whitish microtomentum, remainder of thorax polished (as in 
Fig. 13
). Abdomen, rear third of T4 and all of T5 polished; surstylus medium length, parallel sided (
Figs. 53, 54
). Phallus, hypandrium, pre- and postgonite, ejaculatory sclerite, and sternites as in 77, 78, 108–110, 130 respectively.
